{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand,",
    "Bonito is an open-source model that can be used to create tasks with the user's unannotated text without additional API costs.",
    "Recently, Li et al. (2023) proposed to learn a backtranslation model, similar to Bonito, to iteratively grow and refine their instruction tuning dataset (Gulcehre et al., 2023).",
    "However, they focus on generating instructions conditioned on the unannotated text from a web corpus for long-form conversational data where the answer to the instruction is the unannotated text.",
    "In contrast, we focus on generating NLP tasks conditioned on a task type and unannotated text from a specialized domain."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Recently, Li et al. (2023) proposed to learn a backtranslation model, similar to Bonito, to iteratively grow and refine their instruction tuning dataset (Gulcehre et al., 2023)."
  ]
}